49
00:04:20,293 --> 00:04:21,983
- Yasu!
- to please board the train now.

50
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:25,963
Why can't I say these few words?

51
00:04:27,033 --> 00:04:30,993
Because... you've chosen
your path in life.

52
00:04:31,803 --> 00:04:34,863
And Nobu has a great future
ahead of him.

53
00:04:36,343 --> 00:04:37,433
I can't say it.

54
00:04:39,013 --> 00:04:42,203
So you hafta wish for it yourself.

55
00:04:43,783 --> 00:04:44,473
Nana.

56
00:04:49,083 --> 00:04:49,983
Don't go.

57
00:04:53,623 --> 00:04:54,753
It'll be lonely without you.

58
00:05:01,533 --> 00:05:03,963
Stop messing with me!
Then you come with me!

59
00:05:07,003 --> 00:05:10,563
I guess negotiations break off there.
Oh well, good luck.

60
00:05:10,643 --> 00:05:13,233
Yasu! There are law firms in Tokyo, too!

61
00:05:14,143 --> 00:05:16,113
You can sing in this town, too.

62
00:05:28,363 --> 00:05:30,923
But there is no big stage like
the Tokyo Dome or Budokan here.

63
00:05:38,533 --> 00:05:40,403
Think of it as a foolish dream
if you want.

64
00:05:41,903 --> 00:05:45,243
But one day, I will definitely perform
on a big stage.

65
00:05:45,943 --> 00:05:47,883
I'll perform before
an incredible number of spotlights

66
00:05:47,943 --> 00:05:49,143
and amount of cheering,

67
00:05:49,413 --> 00:05:51,543
and earn so much money
I won't know how to spend it.

68
00:05:53,353 --> 00:05:56,283
I'm not some princess
who is satisfied just singing.

69
00:05:58,023 --> 00:06:00,423
Singing is my means to live.

70
00:06:01,163 --> 00:06:03,223
So one day, I'll definitely...

71
00:06:07,663 --> 00:06:09,463
What? Who?

72
00:06:09,973 --> 00:06:12,333
And, how long does she intend
to stay on top of me?

73
00:06:14,443 --> 00:06:15,303
Are you all right?

74
00:06:16,243 --> 00:06:17,973
I'm fine. Sorry!

75
00:06:19,813 --> 00:06:24,143
I'll never forget that day.
March 5th, 2001.

76
00:06:24,353 --> 00:06:25,683
My twentieth birthday.

77
00:06:26,823 --> 00:06:28,343
That's the day I met you.

78
00:06:32,453 --> 00:06:35,183
That stupid Demon Lord!

79
00:06:35,363 --> 00:06:37,223
It's nothing to cry about.

80
00:06:37,293 --> 00:06:39,763
But I was really looking forward
to the fireworks!

81
00:06:39,863 --> 00:06:42,993
I even withdrew cash from
my savings to buy a yukata to wear!

82
00:06:43,333 --> 00:06:46,173
So you finally dipped
into Natsuko's 300,000 yen.

83
00:06:49,073 --> 00:06:51,203
We met on the train to Tokyo,

84
00:06:51,273 --> 00:06:53,643
I ended up moving in together
with Nana Komatsu.

85
00:06:54,213 --> 00:06:56,043
Nickname Hachi, or Hachiko.

86
00:06:56,553 --> 00:07:00,713
Hachiko is selfish,
overly dependent and cries easily.

87
00:07:01,053 --> 00:07:03,573
She is completely boy crazy

88
00:07:03,653 --> 00:07:05,143
and she's quick to switch over.

89
00:07:05,623 --> 00:07:07,323
She's only been in Tokyo
for six months

90
00:07:07,393 --> 00:07:09,193
and she's already dating a third guy.

91
00:07:09,663 --> 00:07:10,493
Nobu...

92
00:07:11,033 --> 00:07:14,263
But she would remain uncorrupted.
She was a strange woman.

93
00:07:17,333 --> 00:07:20,563
Typhoon Eleven, which has made
its way onto land in the Kanto region,

94
